It's not fair to use astronauts as guinea pigs. Instead scientist are sending miniature human organs on chips to the International Space Station 
(ISS). SpaceX, founded by entrepreneur Elon Musk, sent four microchips 
embedded with living human cells to the ISS. This strange payload was part of an experiment by the 
Tissue Chips in Space Initiative. The project is studying how the human body is affected by microgravity. RARE FOOTAGE: This stunning time-lapse video of our planet shows wispy clouds disappear into the shadows Moonlit time-lapse taken from the window of the International Space Station over Africa and the Mediterranean, captures the earth below in spectacular detail. 